When adding an @mention, it is rendered in a different way in the preview of a page and in the page itself. The difference is that the text in the page will not be wrapped at the end of the line but that is not the case in the preview.

The cause for this is the following CSS is applied only when displaying a page but not in the preview:
{code}
.wiki-content .user-mention {
   ...
   white-space: nowrap;
   ...
}
{code}

Also, in the page, the @mention has an @ symbol and it is in a box. In the preview mode it is just displayed as a normal link.

*+Workaround:+*
You can get the @mentions displayed in the same way they do in the preview by applying the following CSS in your stylesheets:
{code}.user-mention {  
   white-space: normal !important;  
   border: none !important;  
}  
  
.wiki-content .user-mention:before, .wiki-content .user-mention:hover:before, .wiki-content .user-mention:active:before, .wiki-content .user-mention:visited:before {  
   content: none !important;  
}{code}

