When I set the default theme to the great new Confluence theme, I feel instant happiness and a warm feeling of joy... when I open it in my Chrome browser.

When I take a look at the same page in Internet Explorer 8, I feel a little bit sad, because the fonts are not correctly rendered in the sidebar:

!confluence-sidebar-wrong-font-family.png!

I also tried on a machine of a colleague, to be sure it was a problem on only my machine. Unfortunately, the great-looking sidebar was also a bit on the ugly side over there.

I took a look at the CSS styling and found out the _acs-side-bar_ class overrides the basic font-family property (Arial, sans serif) with sans serif. Due to some strange thing, the default Sans Serif font on our Windows machines are rather ugly, hence the results.

!wrong-font-family-cascade.png!

I could fix this by adding the following line to the custom Confluence HTML:

{code}
<script type="text/javascript">
AJS.$(document).ready(function() {
  AJS.$(".acs-side-bar").css("font-family","Arial, sans serif");
});
</script>
{code}

Resulting in:

!confluence-sidebar-fixed-font-family.png!

